svg.text: The See Us Play page only shows information about the next Nanonauts
concert. But they have quite a few concerts coming up and it would be
good if there was a list of these concerts. The list could show:
where the concert is taking place
what time the Nanonauts are playing
how much it will cost to get in
A good way to do this would be to show the information in a table.
To understand how to add the table to the See Us Play web page we need to understand what the different
parts of the table are called. This is shown in the diagram below:
From this we can see that, in HTML, the recipe for a table is:
Add one or more table row elements
Fill each row with table header or table data elements.
The HTML markup elements are named as shown to the right.
